# Gem TD — core conventions

## Docs path (required lookup)

Canonical docs: `E:\Projects\Docs\project-docs\Unity\unity-gem-td`

- Design: `GDD.md`, `ARCHITECTURE.md`, `UI-SPEC.md`
- Plans/status: `planning/`
- Superpowers / SDD ledger: `planning/sdd/` (`progress.md`, task briefs/reports)

**Always read the docs repo** when resuming work, locking designs, or answering “what’s decided / what’s next.” Do not assume absence because the file is not in this Unity workspace.

**Never** create design docs, plans, or `.superpowers/` / SDD scratch inside this game repo. If a skill defaults to `<repo>/.superpowers/sdd`, redirect writes to `…/unity-gem-td/planning/sdd/`.

## Lookup order

Docs repo (absolute path) → SCE (`user-sce`) → Context7 → web. If SCE lacked info that exists only in the docs repo, say what to index.

## Pushback

When a suggestion is suboptimal: (1) acknowledge goal (2) why not (3) better option (4) why better (5) when to revisit.

## Engineering

- No gameplay reflection (`Activator`, attribute scan, string→type).
- ScriptableObject data; plain C# logic; thin views.
- Object pools for enemies/projectiles/pops.
- No `System.Linq` in combat ticks — use `for` / reused lists.
- Git: feature branch + PR into protected `main` only.
- Never `git commit` or `git push` unless the user explicitly asks.
